cf - char filter
default: print only ascii


positive / negative filter string:
	positive: only print instances of individual characters appearing.
	negative: leave out instances of individual characters appearing.

class options are cumulative

character classes:
alphanumeric
digit
space
upper
lower
blank
nonprint
printable
punctuation


c library character class functions
islower -l --lower
isupper -u --upper
isalpha -a --alpha
isdigit -d --digit
isalnum -m --alnum
isxdigit 
ispunct -p --punct
isspace -s --space
isblank -b --blank
isgraph -g --graph
iscntrl -c --control
isascii -

template -t --template

exclusive filter -x --exclusive

binary -B --binary
	treat newlines as a normal char

input file -i --input (stdin)
output file -o --output (stdout)


FUTURE OPTIMIZATION:
 function pointer array that dispatches tests.
